      },
      {
        "number": 70,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المَعَارِجِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ma'aarij",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ascending Stairways",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5376,
            "text": "A beseecher besought the visitation of chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5377,
            "text": "(a chastisement meant) for the unbelievers, one which none can avert;",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5378,
            "text": "a chastisement from Allah, the Lord of the ascending steps,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5379,
            "text": "by which the angels and the Spirit ascend to Him in one Day the duration of which is fifty thousand years.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5380,
            "text": "So, (O Prophet), persevere with gracious perseverance.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5381,
            "text": "Verily they think that the chastisement is far off,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5382,
            "text": "while We think that it is near at hand.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5383,
            "text": "It shall befall on a Day whereon the sky will become like molten brass,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5384,
            "text": "and the mountains will become like dyed tufts of wool,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5385,
            "text": "and no bosom friend will enquire about any of his bosom friends",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5386,
            "text": "although they shall be within sight of one another. The guilty one would fain ransom himself from the torment of that Day by offering his children,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5387,
            "text": "and his spouse and his brother,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5388,
            "text": "and his kinsfolk who had stood by him,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5389,
            "text": "and all persons of the earth, if only he could thus save himself.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5390,
            "text": "By no means! It will be the fierce flame",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5391,
            "text": "that will strip off the scalp.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5392,
            "text": "It shall insistently summon him who turned his back and retreated,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5393,
            "text": "and amassed wealth and covetously hoarded it.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5394,
            "text": "Verily man is impatient by nature:",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5395,
            "text": "bewailing when evil befalls him,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5396,
            "text": "and tight-fisted when good fortune visits him,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5397,
            "text": "except those that pray,",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5398,
            "text": "and are constant in their Prayer;",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5399,
            "text": "and those in whose wealth there is a known right",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5400,
            "text": "for those that ask and those that are dispossessed,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5401,
            "text": "those who firmly believe in the Day of Recompense,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5402,
            "text": "and fear the chastisement of their Lord –",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5403,
            "text": "surely the chastisement of their Lord is a thing none can feel secure from –",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5404,
            "text": "and those who guard their private parts,",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5405,
            "text": "except in regard to their spouses and those whom their right hands possess, for in regard to them they are not reproachable,",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5406,
            "text": "but any who seeks to go beyond that, it is indeed they who are the transgressors,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5407,
            "text": "and those who fulfil their trusts and their covenants,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5408,
            "text": "and those who are upright in their testimonies;",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5409,
            "text": "and who take due care of their Prayer:",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5410,
            "text": "all these shall live honourably in the Gardens.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5411,
            "text": "But what is the matter with the unbelievers who are hurrying towards you",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5412,
            "text": "in crowds, both on the right and on the left?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5413,
            "text": "Does everyone of them wish to enter the Garden of Bliss?",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5414,
            "text": "By no means! They know that which We have created them from.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5415,
            "text": "I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that We have the power",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5416,
            "text": "to replace them by others who would be better than they; and We shall certainly not be overpowered.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5417,
            "text": "So leave them to engage in vain talk and to amuse themselves until they come face to face with the Day which they are promised,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5418,
            "text": "the Day on which they will hastily come forth from their graves, as though they were hurrying on to the altars of their deities.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5419,
            "text": "Their eyes will be downcast and disgrace will overwhelm them. Such is the Day that they were promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 71,
        "name": "سُورَةُ نُوحٍ",
        "englishName": "Nooh",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Noah",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5420,
            "text": "We sent Noah to his people (and directed him): “Warn your people before a grievous chastisement comes upon them.”",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5421,
            "text": "Noah said: “My people, I have certainly been sent as a clear warner to you,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5422,
            "text": "that you serve Allah and fear Him, and follow me;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5423,
            "text": "He will forgive your sins and will grant you respite until an appointed term. Indeed when Allah's appointed term comes, it cannot be deferred; if you only knew!”",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5424,
            "text": "He said: “My Lord, I called my people by night and by day,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5425,
            "text": "but the more I called, the farther they fled.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5426,
            "text": "And every time I called them so that You might forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears and wrapped up their faces with their garments and obstinately clung to their attitude, and waxed very proud.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5427,
            "text": "Then I summoned them openly,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5428,
            "text": "and preached to them in public, and also addressed them in secret.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5429,
            "text": "I said to them: “Ask forgiveness from your Lord; surely He is Most Forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5430,
            "text": "He will shower upon you torrents from heaven,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5431,
            "text": "and will provide you with wealth and children, and will bestow upon you gardens and rivers.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5432,
            "text": "What is amiss with you that you do not look forward to the majesty of Allah",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5433,
            "text": "when He has created you in stages?",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5434,
            "text": "Do you not see how Allah has created seven heavens, one upon the other,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5435,
            "text": "and has placed the moon in them as a light, and the sun as a radiant lamp?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5436,
            "text": "And Allah has caused you to grow out of the earth so wondrously,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5437,
            "text": "and He will later cause you to return to it and will then again bring you out of it.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5438,
            "text": "Allah has made the earth a wide expanse for you",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5439,
            "text": "so that you may tread its spacious paths.”",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5440,
            "text": "Noah said: “My Lord, they did not pay heed to what I said, and followed those (nobles) whose possession of wealth and children has led them to an even greater loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5441,
            "text": "They contrived a plot of great magnitude.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5442,
            "text": "They said: “Do not abandon your deities; do not abandon Wadd, nor Suwa, nor Yaghuth, nor Yauq, nor Nasr.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5443,
            "text": "They have misled many. So do not enable these evildoers to increase in anything except straying (from the Right Way).”",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5444,
            "text": "And so they were drowned on account of their sins, and then cast into the Fire, and did not find any other than Allah, to come forth to their help.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5445,
            "text": "Noah said: “My Lord, do not leave out of these unbelievers even a single dweller on earth,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5446,
            "text": "for certainly if You should leave them (alive), they will mislead Your servants, and will beget none but sinners and utter unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5447,
            "text": "My Lord, forgive me and my parents, and whoever enters my house as a believer, and forgive all believers, both men and women, and do not increase the wrong-doers in anything except perdition.”",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 72,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجِنِّ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jinn",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Jinn",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5448,
            "text": "Say, (O Prophet), it was revealed to me that a band of jinn attentively listened to (the recitation of the Qur'an) and then (went back to their people) and said:",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5449,
            "text": "“We have indeed heard a wonderful Qur'an which guides to the Right Way; so we have come to believe in it, and we will not associate aught with Our Lord in His Divinity”;",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5450,
            "text": "and that “He – exalted be His Majesty – has not taken to Himself either a wife or a son”;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5451,
            "text": "and that “the foolish among us have been wont to say outrageous things about Allah”;",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5452,
            "text": "and that “we had thought that men and jinn would never speak a lie about Allah”,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5453,
            "text": "and that “some from among the humans used to seek protection of some among the jinn, and thus they increased the arrogance of the jinn”;",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5454,
            "text": "and that “they thought, even as you thought, that Allah would never raise anyone (as a Messenger)”;",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5455,
            "text": "and that “we tried to pry (the secrets of) the heaven, but we found it full of terrible guards and shooting meteors”;",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5456,
            "text": "and that “we would take up stations in the heaven to try to hear but anyone who now attempts to listen finds a shooting meteor in wait for him”;",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5457,
            "text": "and that “we do not know whether evil is intended for those on the earth, or whether their Lord intends to direct them to the Right Way”;",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5458,
            "text": "and that “some of us are upright and some of us are otherwise for we follow widely divergent paths”;",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5459,
            "text": "and that “we thought that we will neither be able to frustrate Allah on earth, nor frustrate Him by flight”;",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5460,
            "text": "and that “when we heard the teaching of the Right Way we came to believe in it; he who believes in His Lord shall have no fear of suffering loss or being subjected to any injustice”;",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5461,
            "text": "and that “among us some are Muslims (Those who have submitted to Allah), and some of us are deviant. So those who became Muslims found the Right Course;",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5462,
            "text": "but those who deviated from the Truth, will be the fuel for Hell.”",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5463,
            "text": "If people were to keep firmly to the Right Way, We would have vouchsafed them abundant rain",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5464,
            "text": "so that We might try them through this bounty. Whoso turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will cause him to suffer a grievous chastisement;",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5465,
            "text": "and that “mosques belong to Allah, so do not invoke anyone with Him”;",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5466,
            "text": "and when Allah's servant stood up to call on Him, they well-nigh swarmed him.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5467,
            "text": "Say, (O Prophet): “I call on my Lord alone, and I do not associate aught with Him in His Divinity.”",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5468,
            "text": "Say: “Surely neither it is in my power to hurt you nor to bring you to the Right Way.”",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5469,
            "text": "Say: “None can protect me from Allah, nor can I find a refuge apart from Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5470,
            "text": "(My task is no more than) to deliver Allah's proclamation and His messages. And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger, surely the Fire of Hell awaits him; therein he will abide in perpetuity.”",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5471,
            "text": "(They shall not change their ways) until they see that against which they had been warned, and then they will know whose helpers are weaker and whose supporters are fewer in number.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5472,
            "text": "Say: “I know not whether what you are promised is near or whether my Lord will prolong its term.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5473,
            "text": "He is the Knower of the Unseen, and He does not disclose His Unseen to anyone",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5474,
            "text": "other than to a Messenger whom He chooses (for the bestowal of any part of the knowledge of the Unseen), whereafter He appoints guards who go before him and behind him,",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5475,
            "text": "so that He may know that they have delivered the messages of their Lord. He encompasses in His knowledge their surroundings and keeps a count of all things.”",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 73,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُزَّمِّلِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Muzzammil",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Enshrouded One",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5476,
            "text": "O you the (sleeping) enwrapped one!",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5477,
            "text": "Stand up in Prayer by night, all but a small part of it;",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5478,
            "text": "half of it, or reduce it a little;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5479,
            "text": "or add to it a little; and recite the Qur'an slowly and distinctly.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5480,
            "text": "Behold, We shall cast upon you a Weighty Word.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5481,
            "text": "Surely getting up at night is the best means of subduing the self and is more suitable for uprightness in speech.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5482,
            "text": "You are indeed much occupied during the day with the affairs of the world.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5483,
            "text": "So remember the name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him with exclusive devotion.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5484,
            "text": "He is the Lord of the East and the West; there is no god but He. So take Him alone for your Guardian,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5485,
            "text": "And bear patiently the vain things they utter, and gracefully forsake them.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5486,
            "text": "Leave it to Me to deal with the affluent ones who give the lie (to the Truth), and bear with them for a while.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5487,
            "text": "We have heavy fetters and a blazing Fire in store for them;",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5488,
            "text": "and a food that chokes, and a grievous chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5489,
            "text": "(They will come across all this) on the Day when the earth and the mountains shall tremble violently and the mountains shall crumble into heaps of scattered sand.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5490,
            "text": "Surely We have sent to you a Messenger as a witness over you, just as We had sent a Messenger to Pharaoh.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5491,
            "text": "But Pharaoh disobeyed Our Messenger, so We seized him with a terrible seizing.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5492,
            "text": "If you persist in disbelieving, how will you guard yourself against the (woe of the) Day that will turn children grey-haired,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5493,
            "text": "the Day whose severity shall cause the heaven to split asunder? Allah's promise is ever bound to be fulfilled.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5494,
            "text": "Indeed this is nothing but a Good Counsel; so let him who will take a way leading to his Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5495,
            "text": "(O Prophet), your Lord knows that you sometimes stand up in Prayer nearly two-thirds of the night, and sometimes half or one-third of it, and so does a party of those with you; Allah measures the night and the day. He knows that you cannot keep an accurate count of it, so He has shown mercy to you. So now recite as much of the Qur'an as you can. He knows that there are among you those who are sick and others who are journeying in the land in quest of Allah's bounty, and still others who are fighting in the cause of Allah. So recite as much of the Qur'an as you easily can, and establish Prayer, and pay Zakah, and give Allah a goodly loan. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you shall find it with Allah. That is better and its reward is greater. And ask for Allah's forgiveness; surely He is Most Forgiving, Most Compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 575,
            "ruku": 509,
            "hizbQuarter": 230,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 74,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُدَّثِّرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Muddaththir",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Cloaked One",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
